18/12/2002
ATHENS, Greece -- On Tuesday (17 December), the government presented the priorities it will address when it assumes the rotating EU Presidency on 1 January. Prime Minister Costas Simitis cited EU enlargement as one major objective. He said he hoped the process would proceed as planned and that the ten new members would sign the accession treaty in Athens on 16 April. He also noted the adoption of pre-accession programmes for Bulgaria and Romania, as well as a new association agreement between the EU and Turkey. (Kathimerini - 18/12/02; Athens News Agency, Macedonian News Agency, ERT - 17/12/02)
